HEADWORD: Hortus siccus
<hw>Hor"tus sic"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., a dry
garden.]</ety> <def>A collection of specimens of plants, dried and
preserved, and arranged systematically; an herbarium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

